{
  "_comment": [
    "Starting-point MCP server config for Cursor. The `init` skill copies",
    "this file to .cursor/mcp.json on first run if .cursor/mcp.json is",
    "missing. After init, edit .cursor/mcp.json (not this template) and",
    "add any servers you want. .cursor/mcp.json is gitignored (it may",
    "carry auth tokens); this template stays committed so the repo",
    "self-documents.",
    "",
    "Claude Code users: see the companion template at .mcp.json.claude.",
    "Content is intentionally identical (Superagent has no per-IDE OAuth",
    "client_id constraint, unlike NVIDIA-internal frameworks); only the",
    "destination path differs. Keep .cursor/mcp.json and .mcp.json in",
    "sync by editing one and re-running `init` (which detects drift and",
    "offers to mirror).",
    "",
    "Superagent itself requires no MCP servers for the quick-start. Each",
    "ingestor declares its own MCP / CLI requirements; see",
    "superagent/docs/data-sources.md.",
    "",
    "Common personal-life servers you might wire up here:",
    "  - apple-reminders / apple-notes (via osascript)",
    "  - gmail / google-calendar (Google Workspace MCP)",
    "  - apple-health (healthsync SQLite)",
    "  - plaid / monarch / ynab (finance)",
    "  - whoop / strava / oura / garmin (wearables)",
    "  - home-assistant / tesla (smart-home / vehicles)",
    "  - playwright (browser automation / web smoke tests)",
    "",
    "Each ingestor probes its required source on first run; missing sources",
    "degrade gracefully and never block other ingestors."
  ],
  "mcpServers": {
    "Playwright": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "@playwright/mcp@latest",
        "--user-data-dir",
        ".playwright-superagent",
        "--caps",
        "vision,pdf,devtools"
      ]
    }
  }
}
